Description: In an effort to "thin the herd", up for auction is my Surf Green Squier Cyclone. This guitar was purchased new from a Japanese retailer back in 2012/13. I have owned this guitar since new and has been an in-home only guitar. Always stored in a smoke-free home in it's original gig bag. The Cyclone was only played on occasion and is in excellent condition. The original tremolo arm along with the small parts accessory bag will be included along with the Squier gig-bag. Please review the photographs before bidding as they are a key part of the description. Some of the features;Alder bodyMaple neck24-3/4" scale (Gibson scale)Rosewood fret-board22 medium-jumbo fretsSingle-coil neck pick-upHumbucker bridge pick-upOne tone, one volume3-way switchingSynchronized tremoloGig-bag As with any electric guitar, it will need to be setup to your preferred playing style as everyone has their own comfort zone. This auction is for the lower 48 states in the United States only. As a used guitar it is being sold "as is" with no returns. Again, please review the photographs as a key part of the description before bidding. Item will be shipped within 48 hours after payment baring Sundays and federal holidays. Any bidders with less then ten feedback or excessive negative feedback will need to contact me before bidding. Thank you.
